.TH IB-BOX-SPREAD-TUI 1 "November 2025" "IBKR Box Spread TUI" "User Manuals"
.SH NAME
ib-box-spread-tui \- Terminal User Interface for IBKR Box Spread trading system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ib-box-spread-tui
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBib-box-spread-tui\fR is a terminal-based dashboard for monitoring and managing
the IBKR Box Spread trading system. It provides a real-time view of account status,
positions, orders, and strategy metrics in a familiar top/htop-style interface.

The TUI displays:
.IP \(bu 2
Account metrics (net liquidation, buying power, margin requirements)
.IP \(bu 2
Active box spread positions with ROI and profit metrics
.IP \(bu 2
Real-time option chain data and Greeks
.IP \(bu 2
Order status and execution history
.IP \(bu 2
System alerts and notifications
.IP \(bu 2
Strategy status and controls

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-endpoint " " \fIURL\fR
REST API endpoint URL (default: http://localhost:8080/api/snapshot)
.TP
.BR \-\-interval " " \fISECONDS\fR
Polling interval in seconds (default: 1)
.TP
.BR \-\-mock
Use mock data provider for offline testing
.TP
.BR \-\-nautilus
Use Nautilus Trader data provider

.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Tab / Shift+Tab
Cycle focus across tabs (Dashboard, Positions, History, Orders, Alerts)
.TP
.B Arrow Keys
Navigate and scroll within lists and tables
.TP
.B Enter
Open detail popup for selected row/item
.TP
.B S
Start or resume trading strategy
.TP
.B T
Stop trading strategy gracefully
.TP
.B K
Cancel all open strategy orders
.TP
.B D
Toggle dry-run mode (safe simulation mode)
.TP
.B B
Buy combo: Submit additional box spread to lower cost basis
.TP
.B Shift+S
Sell combo: Submit offsetting spread to realize gains
.TP
.B ?
Show keyboard shortcuts help
.TP
.B Q
Quit TUI

.SH TABS

.SS Dashboard
Main overview showing:
.IP \(bu 2
Account summary (net liquidation, buying power, margin)
.IP \(bu 2
Symbol watchlist with current prices and ROI
.IP \(bu 2
Active positions summary
.IP \(bu 2
Recent orders
.IP \(bu 2
System status indicators (TWS, ORATS, Portal, QuestDB)

.SS Current Positions
Detailed view of open box spread positions:
.IP \(bu 2
Strike prices and expiration dates
.IP \(bu 2
Net debit and theoretical value
.IP \(bu 2
Arbitrage profit and ROI percentage
.IP \(bu 2
Days to expiration
.IP \(bu 2
Maker/taker counts and rebate estimates
.IP \(bu 2
APR vs benchmark comparison

.SS Historic Positions
Recently closed positions from QuestDB and strategy history:
.IP \(bu 2
Closed position details
.IP \(bu 2
Realized profit/loss
.IP \(bu 2
Execution timestamps
.IP \(bu 2
Performance metrics

.SS Orders
Timeline of all orders:
.IP \(bu 2
Order submission time
.IP \(bu 2
Order status (pending, filled, cancelled, rejected)
.IP \(bu 2
Fill details and prices
.IP \(bu 2
Order type and parameters

.SS Alerts
Scrollable notification feed:
.IP \(bu 2
System alerts (info, warning, error, success)
.IP \(bu 2
Strategy notifications
.IP \(bu 2
Connection status updates
.IP \(bu 2
Risk limit warnings

.SH DATA SOURCES

The TUI can connect to multiple data sources:

.TP
.B REST API (default)
Polls REST endpoints shared with iPad/web frontends for:
.IP \(bu 2
Strategy status
.IP \(bu 2
Positions and account data
.IP \(bu 2
Orders and executions
.IP \(bu 2
Alerts and notifications

.TP
.B Mock Provider
Generates synthetic data for offline testing and development.
Useful for UI development without backend connection.

.TP
.B Nautilus Trader
Integration with Nautilus Trader for advanced market data
and execution capabilities.

.SH COLOR SCHEME

The TUI uses color coding for quick visual feedback:

.TP
.B Green
Positive values, healthy status, profitable positions
.TP
.B Red
Negative values, errors, losses
.TP
.B Yellow
Warnings, margin requirements, benchmarks
.TP
.B Cyan
Headers, maker counts, system OK status
.TP
.B Magenta
Taker counts, commissions
.TP
.B Blue
Informational messages

.SH EXAMPLES

Start TUI with default REST endpoint:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ib-box-spread-tui
.fi
.RE

Use mock data for offline testing:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ib-box-spread-tui --mock
.fi
.RE

Connect to custom REST endpoint:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ib-box-spread-tui --endpoint http://localhost:3000/api/snapshot --interval 2
.fi
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.TP
.B TUI_ENDPOINT
Default REST API endpoint URL (overridden by --endpoint)
.TP
.B TUI_INTERVAL
Default polling interval in seconds (overridden by --interval)
.TP
.B TERM
Terminal type (auto-detected, affects color support)

.SH FILES

.TP
.B ~/.config/ib-box-spread/tui.json
User configuration file (if implemented)
.TP
.B /tmp/ib-box-spread-tui.log
Log file location (if logging enabled)

